At Robert Mueller’s hearings, lawmakers expected a showdown.

How to buy carbon offsets.

Epstein Used the Billionaire Behind Victoria’s Secret for Wealth and Women

  • The financier Jeffrey Epstein, charged with sex trafficking, cultivated a yearslong relationship with Leslie Wexner and proceeded to become extraordinarily rich.
  • Mr. Wexner’s colleagues were mystified as to why a renowned businessman would place so much trust in an outsider like Mr. Epstein.

Russian Hack of Elections System Was Far-Reaching, Report Finds

  • Election systems in all 50 states were targeted by Russian hackers in 2016, the Senate Intelligence Committee concluded.
  • But the report was so heavily redacted that key lessons for 2020 were blacked out.

Mueller Testimony Deepens Democratic Divide on Impeachment

Some lawmakers are pushing for formal impeachment hearings soon, while moderates are pleading that the party rest its case against President Trump.

The president’s written testimony is becoming additional fodder for Democrats debating impeachment.

Automakers, Rejecting Trump Pollution Rule, Strike a Deal With California

  • Four of the world’s largest automakers struck a deal with the nation’s largest auto market to reduce tailpipe pollution.
  • The move is a blow to the Trump administration, which is preparing to roll back national vehicle pollution standards and revoke states’ rights to set their own such rules.

U.S. to Resume Executions After a 16-Year Break

  • The federal government will resume executions of death-row inmates for the first time since 2003, Attorney General William Barr said.
  • The announcement reverses what had been essentially a moratorium on the federal death penalty.
903 comments

These are the five men the government plans to execute.

Divided House Passes 2-Year Budget Deal to Raise Spending

Republicans defected by the dozens, despite President Trump’s endorsement and pressure from key outside groups, and Democrats were left to get the deal passed.

In Europe, Record-Breaking Heat and Rare Relief

  • A heat wave scorched Europe, with temperatures nearing 110 degrees in Paris. Fountains and misters provided reprieve, yet air conditioners were hard to find.
  • The technology that transformed American buildings over the last century is still shunned in much of the Continent.
361 comments

Booker Joins Harris in Clashing With Biden Over Race Before Debate

  • Senators Cory Booker and Kamala Harris have mounted a direct challenge to Joe Biden in hopes of undermining his standing with black voters.
  • “If they want to argue about the past, I can do that,” Mr. Biden said. Early polling shows many black voters remain unmoved.
